#Subsampling Loading the original FastQ files was not possible due their huge size (R2 is 27gb, while the preprocessing is optimized for files under 2gb). We have to downsample our barcode fastqfiles to 100M reads:

Chris Mcginnis suggested running this command on the console:

gunzip R1_001.fastq.gz gunzip R2_001.fastq.gz paste R1_001.fastq R2_001.fastq | awk { printf(%s,$0); n++; if(n%4==0) { printf();} else { printf();} } | awk -v k=100000000 BEGIN{srand(systime() + PROCINFO[pid]);}{s=x++<k?x- 1:int(rand()x);if(s<k)R[s]=$0}END{for(i in R)print R[i]} | awk -F" {print $1$3$5$7 > R1_sub_100M.fastq;print $2$4$6$8 > R2_sub_100M.fastq} gzip R1_sub_100M.fastq gzip R2_sub_100M.fastq gunzip TGACCAAT_S5_L001_R1_001.fastq.gz gunzip TGACCAAT_S5_L001_R2_001.fastq.gz paste TGACCAAT_S5_L001_R1_001.fastq TGACCAAT_S5_L001_R2_001.fastq | awk { printf(%s,$0); n++; if(n%4==0) { printf();} else { printf(");} } | awk -v k=100000000 BEGIN{srand(systime() + PROCINFO[pid]);}{s=x++<k?x- 1:int(rand()x);if(s<k)R[s]=$0}END{for(i in R)print R[i]} | awk -F{print $1$3$5$7 > TGACCAAT_S5_L001_R1_sub_100M.fastq;print $2$4$6$8 > TGACCAAT_S5_L001_R2_sub_100M.fastq} gzip TGACCAAT_S5_L001_R1_sub_100M.fastq gzip TGACCAAT_S5_L001_R2_sub_100M.fastq

David Wu suggested a simpler and faster alternative:

k = 100000000 seqtk sample TGACCAAT_S5_L001_R2_001.fastq $100000000 > TGACCAAT_S5_L001_R2_001_subsampled.fastq gzip TGACCAAT_S5_L001_R1_001_subsampled.fastq - Davids suggestion didnt work, checked seqtk documentation and used the following code:

gunzip TGACCAAT_S5_L001_R2_001.fastq.gz gunzip TGACCAAT_S5_L001_R1_001.fastq.gz seqtk sample -s100 TGACCAAT_S5_L001_R2_001.fastq 100000000 > TGACCAAT_S5_L001_R2_001_subsampled.fastq seqtk sample -s100 TGACCAAT_S5_L001_R1_001.fastq 100000000 > TGACCAAT_S5_L001_R1_001_subsampled.fastq gzip TGACCAAT_S5_L001_R2_001_subsampled.fastq gzip TGACCAAT_S5_L001_R1_001_subsampled.fastq

gunzip ACAGTGAT_S6_L001_R1_001.fastq.gz gunzip ACAGTGAT_S6_L001_R2_001.fastq.gz seqtk sample -s100 ACAGTGAT_S6_L001_R1_001.fastq 100000000 > ACAGTGAT_S6_L001_R1_001_subsampled.fastq seqtk sample -s100 ACAGTGAT_S6_L001_R2_001.fastq 100000000 > ACAGTGAT_S6_L001_R2_001_subsampled.fastq gzip ACAGTGAT_S6_L001_R2_001_subsampled.fastq gzip ACAGTGAT_S6_L001_R1_001_subsampled.fastq

bar.table_sweep.list.b1 <- list()
n <- 0
for (q in seq(0.01, 0.99, by=0.02)) {
  print(q)
  n <- n + 1
  bar.table_sweep.list.b1[[n]] <- classifyCells(bar.table.b1, q=q)
  names(bar.table_sweep.list.b1)[n] <- paste("q=",q,sep="")
}
